  [1mRoot Cause:[22m The program crashes due to a [1mNULL pointer dereference[22m. The
  [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m field in the Student structure is [38;2;177;185;249mNULL[39m (0x0000000000000000), but
  the code attempts to write to [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores][39m without first
  allocating memory for the scores array.

  [1mDetailed Analysis:[22m
  - [1mWhere:[22m The crash occurs at line 26: [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores] = score;[39m
  - [1mWhy:[22m The Student structure was created with [38;2;177;185;249mscores = NULL[39m, but no
  memory was allocated for the scores array before attempting to store
  score values
  - [1mCall Stack:[22m main() â†’ add_score() â†’ crash on NULL pointer access
  - [1mVariables at crash:[22m
    - [38;2;177;185;249ms->name = "Alice"[39m
    - [38;2;177;185;249ms->age = 20[39m
    - [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores = 0x0000000000000000[39m (NULL)
    - [38;2;177;185;249ms->num_scores = 0[39m
    - [38;2;177;185;249mscore = 95.5[39m

  [1mThe Fix:[22m The [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student[39m function should allocate memory for the
  scores array, or the [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m function should check if scores is NULL
  and allocate memory as needed before attempting to store values.
